I just often wonder what is available in general (not to reinvent the wheel): normally if there's a generated scaladoc, it may be enough or (more often) I just check the sources and see the "global symbols outline" ðŸ˜„ but with this "macrofull" code it's kind of hard (I'm also very superficially familiar with macros). 
Another thing that bothers me is that I don't understand how code is organized in the scalameta repo. Probably there is some development dcoumentation for it that I didn't find?

